    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1312"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/73.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Hostetter</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department informed that Sinaloa authorities have imposed war levy five thousand
                    pesos per month on Almada Sugar Refineries Company. Evidence in possession of
                    Department appears to show that this company which owns Navolato property is
                    American corporation organized October 1901 under laws of State of New York and
                    that soon after organization it bought said property; that stock of company is
                    almost entirely owned by Almada Sugar Corporation organized under laws of State
                    of Delaware; that over five hundred thousand dollars American money has been
                    invested in said property.</p>
                <pb facs="0890" n="774" xml:id="pg_774"/>
                <p>Endeavor to bring above information to attention of Governor Riveros and protest
                    against above imposition on this American company.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
